The purpose of this directory is to contain Cucumber tests for Catroid, run
via calabash-android.

SETUP:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You should use RVM with the .rvmrc provided in this directory.

Install Ruby (http://www.ruby-lang.org)
Install RVM (https://rvm.io)
Install Cucumber (http://rubygems.org/gems/cucumber)
Install Python (for the run-script, http://www.python.org)

You may also need to install bundler (http://rubygems.org/gems/bundler) if you
don't have it. It is required to build the calabash-android gem.

RUNNING TESTS:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Very first test: python run.py -c -b -bc
Makes a clean Catroid build, builds and installs calabash-android and runs it.

Repeated testing: python run.py -b
(Re)build Catroid and run calabash-android.
